.so ../macros
.TH "bk edit" 1 08/18/00 "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk edit \- check out a file for editing (writable)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk edit
.BI [ -q
.B ]
.BI [ files...
.BI | \ -
.B ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Use
.B edit
when modifying existing files. 
.B Edit
checks the file out of the SCCS directory in a read-write mode
and locks the file for modifications.
.LP
.B Edit
with no options will check out all files in a directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -q
run quietly
.SH NOTE
.B edit
is actually an alias for
.B bk get -e
.SH SEE ALSO
.SA co 1
.br
.SA get 1
.br
.SA new 1
.SH CATEGORY
.B Basics
